  body

    article

      section
        h2 The Wow of Genetic Algorithms
        br
        h3 By Roey Chasman

      section
        h2 What Are Genetic Algorithms?
        br
        p Genetic Algorithms use evolutionary principles to 'evolve' and 'adapt' based on environments to some truth, prediction, or optimization.

      section
        h2 DNA and Genes
        br
        p Genetic Algorithms (GA) are modeled after biological reproduction. There are metaphors seen in nature.
        ul
          li 'Genes' are a metaphor for features or traits in a problem space.
          li Collectively Genes are referred to as 'DNA'
          li GA's recombinate Genes in DNA to hopefully evolve better and better solutions.
          li Applying GA means carefully selecting the problem features to use in your DNA.

      section
        h2 Implementation
        br
        p While not necesarily 'easy', they follow a simple series of steps to implement.
        ol
          li I. Genesis
          li II. Fitness
          li III. Reproduction
          li IV. Death

      section
        h2 Initial Seed
        canvas#alpha(data-processing-sources="scripts/walker.pde scripts/drawing.pde")
        span
          button#pauser(onClick='pause()') Pause
          button(onClick='reset()') Reset

      section
        h2 Responsive Slides
